on android, vim /system/usr/keylayout/Generic.kl
key 58 CTRL_LEFT

on linux, 
su
dumpkeys > key.map
vim key.map
keycode 58 = Control
loadkeys key.map
then re-login, it will work

for tty
write it in .bashrc
vim ~/.bashrc
sudo loadkeys $HOME/key.map

for Xorg
vim .xinitrc, put this at the first, 'cause fvwm will stuck at the end
setxkbmap -layout us -option ctrl:nocaps

to revert
loadkeys -d
